p3416
tp3417
a(I0
VWell, he's the troubled hero of Richard Kelly's remarkable debut feature, played by Jake Gyllenhaal.
p3418
tp3419
a(I0
VNot only is Donnie ("Donnie Darko?
p3420
tp3421
a(I0
VWhat the hell kinda name is that?")
p3422
tp3423
a(I0
Va complex character - he's a high IQ high-school student, troubled by mental instability, who is both frank and perspicacious - but the film itself defies genre definition.
p3424
tp3425
a(I0
VIt's a drama about teen love.
p3426
tp3427
a(I0
VIt's philosophical sci-fi.
p3428
tp3429
a(I0
VIt's a satire of 80s America.
p3430
tp3431
a(I0
VAnd more.
p3432
tp3433
a(I0
VIt's 1988.
p3434
tp3435
a(I0
VDonnie wakes up on a mountain road.
p3436
tp3437
a(I0
VIt looks like Provence, but Donnie soon descends into manicured all-American suburbia.
p3438
tp3439
a(I0
VThe film was shot in LA but the fictional setting of Middlesex, Virginia, is reminiscent of Blue Velvet or even E.T.
p3440
tp3441
a(I0
V(further evoked by the presence of Barrymore, who executive produced and co-stars as a teacher).
p3442
tp3443
a(I0
VThese connections - and explicit references within the film to Back To The Future, The Evil Dead and The Last Temptation Of Christ - are all part of Kelly's dense weave, contributing to the film's themes of 80s culture, time travel, the supernatural (Donnie is visited repeatedly by a eerie, man-sized 'rabbit' called Frank - a nod to Harvey) and faith.
p3444
tp3445
a(I0
VQuestions of faith are played out not only through the fundamentalist  undercurrents in Donnie's community (a repressed teacher insists on  banning Graham Greene's 'The Destructors' on the grounds that it  encourages youth violence), but also in the form of a self-help guru,  Jim Cunningham (Swayze).
p3446
tp3447
a(I0
VDonnie's frustration pours out when he's  confronted by this man, who simplistically reduces emotion to a struggle  between fear and love.
p3448
tp3449
a(I0
VIt's a potent stand-off, between reductive  quasi-philosophy from Cunningham (the product of a cynical, quick-fix  commercial culture) and straightforward wisdom from the "troubled and  confused" Donnie.
p3450
tp3451
a(I0
VAs with Paul Thomas Anderson's Magnolia, another product of a young auteur, Donnie Darko is brimfull of ideas.
p3452
tp3453
a(I0
VHowever, Kelly's film focuses on one character,  has a sci-fi dimension and an 80s milieu - which is thankfully created  with sensitivity (no naff wardrobe, plenty of decent period music) and  satirical humour (Dukakis versus Bush Sr forms a backdrop).
p3454
tp3455
a(I0
VDonnie Darko is a well-made film, without tangible low-budget  problems (it cost $4.5 million).
p3456
tp3457
a(I0
VIt's shot with grace and atmosphere,  directed with assurance and expertly played.
p3458
tp3459
a(I0
VAlongside star Gyllenhaal,  his sister Maggie plays his screen sister; expressive character actor  Holmes Osborne plays his bewildered dad; Oscar-nominated Mary McDonnell  plays his mum ("How does it feel to have a wacko for a son?"
p3460
tp3461
